OL,4,CDon't trust caller ID on phones, says
OL,5,COfcom
OL,6, The UK telecoms regulator is warning
OL,7, the public not to trust caller ID on
OL,8, their phones as it tries to help stop
OL,9, people becoming victims of fraud.
OL,11,FSpeaking to BBC Radio 4's Money Box,
OL,12,FHuw Saunders, a director at Ofcom, says
OL,13,Fcaller ID should not be used as a means
OL,14,Fof verifying a caller's identification.
OL,16,FFraudsters are increasingly changing
OL,17,Ftheir caller ID to disguise their
OL,18,Fidentity, known as number spoofing.
OL,20,F"This problem is global in its scope,"
OL,21,Fsays Mr Saunders.
